name: Philly
description: Philadelphia roll is a makizushi (also classified as a kawarizushi)[1] type of sushi generally made with smoked salmon, cream cheese, and cucumber.[2] It can also include other ingredients, such as other types of fish,[3] avocado,[4] scallions,[5] and sesame seed. Like many Western-inspired sushi rolls, the ingredients and name are based on an American market

name: Cali
description: The main wrapped ingredients are the avocado and crab meat,[3] or imitation crab (surimi crab), and the optional mayonnaise; these are all typically wrapped with seaweed, although soy paper can be used.[4] The cucumber may have been used since the beginning,[5] or added later,[6] depending on the account. The inside-out roll may be sprinkled on the outside with sesame seeds; tobiko (flying fish roe),[7][8] or masago (capelin roe) may be used.

name: Rainbow
description: The rainbow roll is considered as the next step of sushi introduction into the United States culinary culture after the California roll, the first roll with nori seaweed leaf hidden inside rice.[3] While the California roll uses no raw fish at all, the rainbow roll takes it one step further by adding raw tuna, salmon, shrimp, and white fish.

name: Spicy Tuna
description: A Spicy tuna roll is a makizushi roll that usually contains raw tuna, and spicy mayo or sriracha. The roll is often seasoned with Ichimi togarashi (ground Red chile powder).

name: Dragon
description: The traditional dragon roll sushi is made of shrimp tempura and cucumber which are tucked inside the nori and with thinly avocado slices which are layered on top of the sushi roll. The main reason for the name of dragon roll sushi is when itâ€™s sliced, the artistically arranged sushi resembles the scales of a dragon. The dragon roll sushi is usually topped with Tobiko or Masago roes and drizzled with spicy mayonnaise and unagi sauce, some recipes use masago sauce or tobiko sauce because they contain mayo and other spicy ingredients. This mixture will give dragon sushi a spicy texture.
